  "response": "George Lucas, the creator of *Star Wars*, has generally kept his opinions about the newer *Star Wars* films relatively private. However, there have been a few insights into his thoughts on *Rogue One: A Star Wars Story* (2016). \n\nIn an interview with filmmaker James Cameron, Lucas mentioned that he felt the newer *Star Wars* films, including *Rogue One*, were \u201cretro\u201d and focused heavily on fan service rather than pushing the story forward in new and innovative ways. While he didn\u2019t explicitly criticize *Rogue One*, his comments suggest he felt the film leaned into nostalgia and familiar elements rather than exploring fresh territory, which was a hallmark of his own approach to storytelling.\n\nThat said, *Rogue One* has been widely praised by fans and critics for its unique tone, gritty portrayal of the *Star Wars* universe, and its strong ties to the original 1977 film, *A New Hope*. While Lucas\u2019s exact thoughts on *Rogue One* remain somewhat ambiguous, his broader perspective on the newer films indicates a preference for innovation over nostalgia.",
